'RAM.EXTEND.B'; WHEN RUN; WILLCREATE   A FILE CALLED 'RAM.EXTEND'.BRUN THIS  FILE TO MODIFY /RAM SO ITCAN HOLD 51   FILES IN ITS VOLUMEDIRECTORY INSTEADOF THE USUAL LIMIT OF 12.  INADDITION; /RAM WILL BE READABLE FROMBASIC.BE SURE TO 'BRUN RAM.EXTEND' BEFOREFILES ARE SAVED TO /RAM; AS /RAM ISDELETED WHEN THE PROGRAM IS RUN.